@NODE item_about "About Solitaire"
@PREV main
@NEXT main
@TOC main

About Solitaire
***************

 This implementaion of the card game Solitaire, was adapted from the
PC version which is bundeled with Windows @{i}(c) Microsoft@{ui} 3.0+.
It is one of the best and most addictive "GUI" games I have ever played.
But since I am no real PC fan (no offence), I just had to make a Amiga
version that was at least as good as the Windows version.

 To be able to to that, I had to get hold of a "REAL computer",
so I bought a A4000-030. This is really the first computer I have 
ever had, which would enable me to write the "Ultimate Solitaire".
(You really can't imagine how horrible it is to write programs on
an diskbased A500!!!).

 I decided to write this program in C, because it's really the best and
simplest way to write system-friendly software. And since it demands
that you at least have an A1200 (KickStart 3.0 & AGA-chipset), 
speed wasn't that important.


@{b}This version of solitaire was developed with:@{ub}
  * SAS/C 6.2, SAS/C 6.3 (really the only choice..)
  * CygnusED V3.5
  * Toolmaker V1.19
  * DOPUS V4.01, DOPUS V4.10 (it really is the ultimate directory utility)
  * DeluxePaint V4.5, V4.6


Read the @{" Credits " link item_credits} section for further "information".
Read the @{" About me " link item_about_me} section for further information about the author.

@ENDNODE

